    "body": "### Problem\n\nI was trying to update my config to v0.12 and after enabling ui2 with `cmdheight=0`, macro recording stopped working. I have seen reports around it not show up on UI, but this time I can confirm it is not recording. Furthermore, I tried on master with minimal config of just `cmdheight=0`, no `ui2` involvement, and I still couldn't record macros.\n\nI have tried to look for issues/comments around the same, but couldn't find any, hence the report.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```sh\nnvim  --clean --cmd \"set cmdheight=0\"\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIt should allow me to record macro regardless\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.13.0-dev-519+g7d99104058\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 15.7.4\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nghostty 1.3.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
